        <h2 class="heading-large">Create a DfE Sign-in account</h2>
        <p>A DfE Sign-in account will allow you to access DfE online services. An approver at your organisation will
            need to create an account for you.</p>

        <h2 class="heading-medium">
            What is an approver?
        </h2>
        <p>An approver can create user accounts, add and remove services and update roles within organisations.</p>

        <h2 class="heading-medium">
            Find an approver
        </h2>
        <p>Approver contact details can be provided by: </p>
        <ul class="list list-bullet">
            <li>the headteacher</li>
            <li>the administration team</li>
            <li>the account manager</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="heading-medium">
            There are no approvers at my organisation
        </h2>
        <p>To set up an approver for your organisation please provide a <b>headed, signed letter</b> from the head of your organisation for example, Headteacher
            to the Service Team with the following details:</p>

        <ul class="list list-bullet" style="margin-bottom: 0">
            <li>approver's name</li>
            <li>approver's email address</li>
            <li>organisation name</li>
            <li>organisation URN or DfE Number</li>
        </ul>

        <details>
            <summary><span class="summary">How to find your URN or DfE number</span></summary>
            <div class="panel panel-border-narrow">
                <p>To find your URN or DfE number please visit:</p>
                <p><a href="https://get-information-schools.service.gov.uk">https://get-information-schools.service.gov.uk</a></p>
            </div>
        </details>

        <p style="margin-top: 1.25em;">Once you have compiled this information email it to: <a href="mailto:SA.DFESIGNIN@education.gov.uk">SA.DFESIGNIN@education.gov.uk</a></p>
